    <string name="server_mode_title">SafeOrbit ‚Äî Server Mode</string>
    <string name="server_mode_description">In server mode, the device shares its location, activity, and optionally, an audio stream. Clients connect using the server ID and code to monitor its status in real time.</string>
    <string name="server_mode_how_to_start_title">How to start:</string>
    <string name="server_mode_how_to_start_steps">1. Set a PIN to protect settings.\n2. Grant access to location, microphone, and activity sensor.\n3. Share the ID and code manually or via QR code.\n4. Set desired active and idle intervals.\n5. Start audio streaming (on client request).\n6. The app continues to run even with the screen off (Android 14+ requires special permissions).</string>
    <string name="server_mode_settings_title">Server mode settings:</string>
    <string name="server_mode_settings_list">‚Ä¢ Set or change the PIN code\n‚Ä¢ Configure active and idle intervals\n‚Ä¢ Choose preferred navigation app\n‚Ä¢ Set a server icon (from camera or gallery)\n‚Ä¢ Generate a QR code for client connection\n‚Ä¢ View activity history by steps and modes\n‚Ä¢ Start/stop audio streaming (on request)\n‚Ä¢ Reset device role (requires PIN)</string>
    <string name="server_mode_security_title">Device protection tips:</string>
    <string name="server_mode_security_tips">‚Ä¢ Set up SafeOrbit as a device administrator (via DevicePolicyManager) for auto-start and configuration lock\n‚Ä¢ Use a PIN code and keep it private\n‚Ä¢ Do not force stop the app ‚Äî it runs in the background</string>
